    "description": "Mubadala-backed Lunate Capital, described as Abu Dhabi's first locally founded hedge fund, is reportedly expanding its focus on UAE and regional investment oppo",
    "category": "general",
    "coverUrl": null,
    "body": "# Abu Dhabi's First Homegrown Hedge Fund Bets on UAE Growth\n**TL;DR:** Mubadala-backed Lunate Capital, described as Abu Dhabi's first locally founded hedge fund, is reportedly expanding its focus on UAE and regional investment opportunities as the Gulf continues to attract global financial talent.\n## A New Chapter for Gulf-Based Asset Management?\n\nThe UAE's ambitions to become a global financial hub may be gaining another data point. According to a recent report from Spear's, Lunate Capital — described as Abu Dhabi's first locally founded hedge fund — is looking to expand its presence in the region.\n\nBacked by Mubadala, one of Abu Dhabi's major sovereign wealth funds, Lunate reportedly sees considerable promise in the UAE's evolving investment landscape.\n\n### Why the Gulf?\n\nThe narrative isn't entirely new. Over the past few years, we've seen a steady stream of hedge funds and asset managers either relocating to or establishing operations in Dubai and Abu Dhabi. The reasons frequently cited include:\n\n- Favorable tax treatment\n- A growing regulatory framework designed to attract international capital\n- Geographic positioning between Asian and European markets\n\n### What It Could Mean\n\nWhether Lunate's trajectory signals a broader maturation of the Gulf's homegrown asset management industry remains to be seen. But it's worth watching as the region continues its push to diversify beyond oil revenues.\n\n*We'll continue to monitor developments in this space.*",
